{"warnings":{"parse":{"*":"The value passed for \"page\" contains invalid or non-normalized data. Textual data should be valid, NFC-normalized Unicode without C0 control characters other than HT (\\t), LF (\\n), and CR (\\r)."}},"parse":{"title":"D\u00e9rive","pageid":714602,"revid":848346380,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the psychogeographical concept. For articles related to the English translation of this word, see <a href=\"/wiki/Drift_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Drift (disambiguation)\">Drift</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%;width:18.0em;border:2px solid #ff0000;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-top:0.4em;line-height:1.2em\">Part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Politics\" title=\"Politics\">Politics</a> series on</td></tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;padding-top:0;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;padding:0 0.2em 0.4em;font-size:150%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Situationist_International\" title=\"Situationist International\">Situationists</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;border-bottom:1px solid #C00;background:none;text-align:left;\">Concepts</div><div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center\"><div class=\"hlist\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Proletarian_internationalism\" title=\"Proletarian internationalism\">Internationalism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Anti-art\" title=\"Anti-art\">Anti-art</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Class_consciousness\" title=\"Class consciousness\">Class consciousness</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"